text.__SUMMARY__: Prunus carolinae is one of a species plant in the family Rosaceae and it is endemic to Colombia. Some sources treat it as a synonym of Prunus subcorymbosa.
text.Sources: Calderon, E. (1998). "Prunus carolinae". The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species. IUCN. 1998: e.T38901A10154254. doi:10.2305/IUCN.UK.1998.RLTS.T38901A10154254.en. Retrieved 22 December 2017.
